---
// Kubernetes analogy section — surfaces the architecture doc callout on the homepage
---

<section class="kube">
  <div class="kube-inner">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">FAMILIAR BY DESIGN</div>
    <h2>If you know Kubernetes,<br>you already understand jitsudo.</h2>
    <p class="kube-desc">
      jitsudo follows the same control plane / client architecture as Kubernetes.
      The same mental model applies — just for cloud IAM instead of container workloads.
    </p>

    <div class="table-wrapper">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Kubernetes</th>
            <th>jitsudo</th>
            <th>What it does</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>kube-apiserver</code></td>
            <td><code>jitsudod</code></td>
            <td>The authoritative control plane; source of truth for all state</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>kubectl</code></td>
            <td><code>jitsudo</code> CLI</td>
            <td>The primary human-operated client</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Operators, webhooks</td>
            <td>MCP agents, approval bots</td>
            <td>Programmatic clients using the same API</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>RBAC</td>
            <td>OPA policy engine</td>
            <td>Defines who can do what, and under what conditions</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>etcd</td>
            <td>PostgreSQL</td>
            <td>Persistent, consistent state store</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <a href="/docs/architecture/overview/" class="kube-link">Read the architecture overview →</a>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .kube {
    padding: 5rem 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2d31;
  }

  .kube-inner {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .section-eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: #f97316;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #f8fafc;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .kube-desc {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #94a3b8;
    line-height: 1.65;
    max-width: 540px;
    margin: 0 auto 2.5rem;
  }

  .table-wrapper {
    overflow-x: auto;
    border: 1px solid #2a2d31;
    border-radius: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    text-align: left;
  }

  thead tr {
    background: #1c1e22;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2d31;
  }

  th {
    padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #64748b;
  }

  td {
    padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
    color: #cbd5e1;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #1e2025;
  }

  tr:last-child td {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  tr:hover td {
    background: #1c1e22;
  }

  code {
    font-family: 'Fira Code', 'Cascadia Code', 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: #7dd3fc;
    background: #0f1e33;
    padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .kube-link {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #f97316;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .kube-link:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    h2 {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }
  }
</style>
